We have commented on your case (15575166). Please find the details below:
Letting you know that I updated the case on 13Apr and you can check my comments in Support Portal for details. In case you missed it, here's my reply:
Created By: Paula Belangoy (4/13/2020 11:24 AM UTC&#43
Thanks for reaching out! Here are my findings why Report D0F3EDC9DE654B6B901C went straight to PID Approval step (Katsuhiko Sakamoto) and skipping Manager Approval (Plate, Juergen).
When I checked inside the workflow, there's a skip step rule placed under Manager Approval step that has these conditions:
Skip rule name: Has Request Attached
Report | Policy | Equal | *Global Travel Expense Policy

Since the expense report has a request attached in it (Request WXEA) and is tagged under '*Global Travel Expense Policy', the report is skipping Manager Approval step and goes directly to PID Approval instead.
Let me know if you have questions. Thank you!

Hello Shelley,

We have commented on your case (15586854). Please find the details below:

Case Comment:

Hi Shelley.

I checked your company??s configuration for Email Reminders and could see that you have two active email reminders for Company Card transactions that are sent to users that have transaction unassigned to a report or assigned to a report that have not yet been submitted. The reminders are for transactions that are 30 and 40 days older. This information is based on the rule set on the email reminder. Also when checking the Email Reminder message, I could see that you already have all tokens available included. The tokens are dynamic texts, such as, in case of Company card email reminder: number of record, list of records, approver, etc. For your email reminders you already have token %4% added, which shows the list of records, presenting the following information:
-Date
-Expense Type
-Vendor
-Amount

Please refer to the guide below, page 14, to see how this List of Records appears on the reminder:
ttps://www.concurtraining.com/customers/tech_pubs/Docs/_Current/SG_Exp/Exp_SG_Email_Reminders.pdf

You can check you Email Reminders by going to Administration >
column56:
Email Reminders. The two email reminders for Company Card Transaction are:
*GW 02-1. Overdue PCard Transactions-30
*GW 02-2. Overdue PCard Transactions-40

So basically, you already have the Emails Reminders configured to show the information you mentioned. :)

I hope I was able to explain everything well. Please reach me back if you have further questions or comments.

Kind Regards.

Maria L??cia
SAP Concur Support

Hi Ryan, thank you so much for the message. We are so honored to have Monadnock Humane Society our platform as a Bloomerang integration customer.??

I sincerely apologize for the technical difficulties you've described with the Hair Ball. As a livestreaming embed platform, Givebutter doesn't restrict anything like video or audio. The issue you're describing seems to be after the video was embedded into Givebutter, and the words ""Unavailable"" confirm that something was misconfigured in your YouTube settings. A common problem is restricting the embed setting on your video on the YouTube side. For example, on YouTube there is a setting called ""embed settings"" where owner of the video can decide whether or not to allow for embeds. It seems like perhaps your privacy settings via YouTube were misconfigured.??

We strive to create the best user experience and are here to help you find success in digital giving. Please let me know if you have any other thoughts or recommendations on how we can help you and others be more successful in the future.??

Best,
Tori??

",edf0b8e82e95c73108dcb3d9e4647e9f,"Hi Ryan, thank you so much for the message. We are so honored to have Monadnock Humane Society our platform as a Bloomerang integration customer.

I sincerely apologize for the technical difficulties you've described with the Hair Ball. As a livestreaming embed platform, Givebutter doesn't restrict anything like video or audio. The issue you're describing seems to be after the video was embedded into Givebutter, and the words ""Unavailable"" confirm that something was misconfigured in your YouTube settings. A common problem is restricting the embed setting on your video on the YouTube side. For example, on YouTube there is a setting called ""embed settings"" where owner of the video can decide whether or not to allow for embeds. It seems like perhaps your privacy settings via YouTube were misconfigured.

We strive to create the best user experience and are here to help you find success in digital giving. Please let me know if you have any other thoughts or recommendations on how we can help you and others be more successful in the future.

column3: This means that they will not be automatically opted in to Expense Assistant. They will not be forced to use it. They only have the option to opt in to this

A: Yes. Under the Available Expenses section, there are several items that you might see:

So, if the actual card transaction has not come in, you may see other items under the Available Expenses section. Of course, if the user has NOT opted in to Expense Assistant, that's a totally different story.

We have commented on your case (11791002). Please see our response below:
Thanks for getting ahead of the game and gathering device data from Lisa
before submitting the ticket-- really appreciate that!
So as I understand it, Lisa wants to attach multiple receipts to one line
item? That's not possible, unfortunately. Itemization is intended for itemization
receipts, so if she has multiple receipts for her hotel stay they don't
really need to be on one itemized line item, even if the charges occurred
For example, if meals are charged to the room and included the final itemized
hotel bill then entered them as itemizations within the hotel expense is
the proper way to do that-- everything is on one receipt, so one line item
with itemizations is the way to go.
If you eat a meal in the restaurant and pay just for that at the time,
that receipt should be a separate line item outside the hotel bill-- with
multiple receipts, multiple separate line items are the way to go.
You should be able to tell if a receipt is attached to an expense by opening
up that expense within your expense report on the app. There will be a
little icon that looks like a scrap of paper next to expenses that have
Thank you for your patience and please let me know if you have any further

column1: <div>Subject: RE: Your Case 11021877 Has Been Updated (Subj: Cannot Get Logged in to the Mobile App)
Subject: Your Case 11021877 Has Been Updated (Subj: Cannot Get Logged in to the Mobile App)
We noticed that you have added a comment to your case (11021877) recently. Please see our response below:

as mentioned, the issue is due to the fact that you have 3 emails in 3 separate entities- 2 in the US datacenter and one in your current EMEA entity- this is not correct, the emails should be unique in Concur.

Because of this,Concur has put in place with the latest releases an automatic search in datacentres in order to prevent duplications of emails or email in one entity that is the same as the login ID in another entity. What this means is that if before, when

manually changing the URL by typing the EMEA one the login worked, now the search is done automatically: the search starts in the US db ALWAYS. If it finds the email there (as it is in this case, it will stop there or it will revert the URL to the US one).

Again,in order to correct the problem we would need to eliminate the 2 identical email addressed from the 2 US entities so that the system would identify your email as the correct one in the EMEA datacenter.
Please advise if i can remove the 2 emails from the CSM entities.
Should you need more information or if this did not fully answer your question, you may update your case via the Concur Support Portal by taking the following steps:

Thank you for contacting SAP Concur admin support regarding this case.
To be able to delete trip segments without creating an expense for it you will need to enable this function in Site Settings.
Click > Administration > Expense > Expense Admin > Site Settings > Tick ""Allow users to remove trip segments without creating expenses"" > Save.
This will allow Tom the ability to delete the trip segment from Available Expenses when they select it.

column1: Case Subject: Japan VAT Rate from October 1, 2019
Case Comment: Alice
1. I have asked the local team for availability to have a call and possibly demo this for you. However demo is not normally given for requested changes.

2. The option to have the user enter the tax amount is a custom field is available but there is no control to determine if the amount entered is accurate. Best practice is to have the user enter the gross amount and have the system calculate.

3. For the custom field it is set up in the tax admin area as well where conditions are introduced where if custom field equals 8 then we use the rate of 8% and if custom field equals 10 then we use rate 10% for example.
4. Correct the system can be set up to calculate only domestic tax.

5. If an expense type only has a single rate then we will code that rate for that expense type to always calculate that rate just like it does today where the user enters gross amount and the tax is calculated. The receipt type would not change how it is calculated
unless you want it to. The field for selecting rate would not be visible to the users for this expense type.
6. The field looks the same as any other field. See screenshot attached of what a field looks like from your current site.

7. The tax data is present in the SAE in the same way that it is present in your current SAE. If you do not have access to your current SAE please create a new support case to have access to this file granted.
Case Description: Hi Team
we would like to seek your advice on the necessary change in Japan Concur to prepare us ready for the change of Japan VAT rate from October 2019, please advise.
Also we would like to explore the feasibility of itemisation by receipt type. examples as follow
1. any update on possibility of a demo session ?
2. Noted, will adopt best practice which is to have the user enter the gross amount and have the system calculate.

3. Base on file attached showing the different rate for each expense type, please assist to set them up on????test instance of Concur so that we could used for this UAT testing to confirm functionality.
Question : in the event that??Receipt Domestic multiple at expense line is selected, will it allow itemisation by 8% & 10%
4. the above should be set up in the system to calculate only domestic tax.

5. Using our attachment for item 3 above, we have set some expense types only has a single rate then Concur will code that rate for that expense type to always calculate that rate just like it does today where the user enters gross amount and the tax is calculated. The receipt type would not change how it is calculated but what if user do not have a receipt, then we should not be apply the tax rate. In such scenario, does it mean that ""no receipt"" has to be selected.??thus the field for selecting rate/receipt type would has to be visible to the users for these expense type. Depend your answer or advice then we would decides if need to set 5 or 3* receipt types below.
6. Thanks for providing screenshot of receipt type field

7. The tax data is present in the SAE in the same way that it is present in our current SAE but we need to know how to generate SAE from UAT environment in order for us to forward it to our IT for testing of import of SAE file to our system to ensure no fallout.
8. We are pending English guide on vat (refer prior 3 link provided on the same case), any update ?

column1: Thanks for contacting Pura Customer Care! My name is Remington and I will be helping you out today!
I read over the email you sent in, I am sorry that you were unaware of the backorder on your order. I would be happy to take a look at the order and see what I can do to help!

It looks like your order contained the fragrance Go Fig-ure, which is currently on back order. This fragrance is expected come back in stock in 1-2 weeks. Once it comes back in stock your order will ship out. You will receive an email with a tracking number.
If do not wish wait for this order I can cancel it for you and replace it with a new order containing an in stock fragrance of your choice in place of Go Fig-ure.
Please let me know how you would like to proceed.
Again I am sorry for the delay. We appreciate your feedback and I will pass it on to the website team. I am hopeful we can change backorder notifications to be more timely.
I have gone ahead and placed a free fragrance order for you including 2 Santal Blush fragrances for you to use while you wait for your order. Your order number is PSI3475566.
Please let me know if you have any other questions!
